    <div align='center'>
        <font size='4'><b>JAMMIN' FASHION</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20100415.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <b>Thursday, April 15, 2010</b> &mdash;
    Loretta Rivers&#039; ears were ringing. She had just come home from a pop concert given by one of her favorite bands, <i>Robotic</i>. &quot;The music was loud, but totally worth it!&quot; she explained. &quot;From cowbells to tambourines, the energy was insane! Not only were my ears ringing, but my head was spinning...with ideas for my new <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">spring fashion line</a>! I came home and started working, and basically didn&#039;t stop until I had some <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">11 new items</a> I couldn&#039;t wait to wear myself!&quot;<br><br>We asked Rivers where the inspiration came from. Smiling, she noted, &quot;If you had been there you would know! The outfits were wild, bright, youthful&mdash;and totally rock and roll. And, since bright colors are usually much needed after a long, gray winter, I&#039;ve decided to release the first half of my collection straight away. So come to the <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">Wearhouse</a> to see what&#039;s new! Then, in another weeks&#039; time, swing by again, when there&#039;ll be a whole fresh crop of items to feast your eyes on!&quot;<br>
<br>
The suspense is going to be tough for Millsberry&#039;s fashionistas, but at least you can get a dose of fun spring threads right now! And, it looks like this first round is already a hit. In fact, over the weekend, Peabody Park was already full of Millsberrians wearing their new clothes and enjoying the nice weather.<br><br>One citizen we spoke with had just come from the Bait Shop. He was wearing a <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">black leather biker vest</a> from Loretta&#039;s line. &quot;This vest is perfect for the months before summer,&quot; he explained. &quot;There&#039;s always a little breeze, so this vest really helps&mdash;and it also looks cool. I was just mistaken for Darren Lancaster from The Wheels (a local rock band), so that made my day!&quot;<br><br>Curious to know what else we saw that&#039;s new for spring? Well, without giving too much away, we can tell you that fun <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">t-shirts</a>, <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">printed leggings</a>, and oversized, <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">pink bow headbands</a> for girls are part of the master plan. Plus, there are <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">classic cardigans</a> for boys, and our all-time favorite for breezy nights: a <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">hooded sweatshirt</a>...with a hood that&#039;s shaped like a crown!<br><br>So head on over to the <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">Wearhouse</a> boutique for a little spring shopping&mdash;and a sampling of Loretta&#039;s favorite band, <i>Robotic</i> (playing on the store&#039;s stereo system, of course!). Just don&#039;t spend all your Millsbucks at once because, like Loretta said, there&#039;ll be more fresh fashion coming your way in one week!
    </div>

